An alleged housebreaker was stopped in his tracks by members of the community and dRK Tactical armed response officers on Monmouth Road in Essenwood, on Monday morning. Spokesperson for dRK Tactical, Kyle Van Reenen, said: “dRK Tactical received an urgent call for assistance for a housebreaking in progress at a residence in Monmouth Road, Essenwood. Armed response officers were immediately dispatched and on arrival a male suspect was apprehended with the assistance of the local community. He said that reports from the scene indicate that the family was arriving home from fetching their granddaughter when they noticed the man on their property and called for assistance. “The suspect was apprehended and handed over to the South African Police Services for further investigation and processing,” added Van Reenen.